{
  "documentMetadata": {
    "title": "Tetanus, Treatment",
    "sourceFile": "Toxin_mediated/Tetanus, Treatment.pdf"
  },
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Clinical Setting"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Spasm of musculature caused by tetanospasmin toxin of the anaerobic bacteria Clostridium tetani. Primary tetanus infection, a clinical diagnosis (cultures often are negative):"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Generalized and persistent, tonic muscle spasms and paroxysms (risus sardonicus, trismus, lockjaw).",
        "Neonatal: generalized weakness, failure to nurse, progression to muscle spasms. May result from rubbing spore-containing dirt on the umbilical stump.",
        "6 treatment steps are outlined below."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Etiologies"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Clostridium tetani (tetanospasmin toxin)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Primary Regimens"
    },
    {
      "type": "nestedContent",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "header",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "6 Steps:"
        },
        {
          "type": "procedure",
          "procedureData": {
            "name": "Urgent endotracheal intubation to protect the airway. Laryngeal spasm is common. Early tracheostomy."
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "drugRegimen",
          "regimenData": {
            "intent": "symptomRelief",
            "components": [
              {
                "drug": "diazepam",
                "dose": "20 mg/kg/day",
                "route": "IV"
              },
              {
                "drug": "midazolam",
                "connector": "or"
              }
            ],
            "notes": "Reports of benefit combining diazepam with magnesium sulfate (Ln 368:1436, 2006). Worst cases: need neuromuscular blockade with vecuronium."
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "drugRegimen",
          "regimenData": {
            "intent": "treatment",
            "components": [
              {
                "drug": "Human hyperimmune globulin",
                "route": "IM"
              },
              {
                "drug": "tetanus toxoid immunization",
                "connector": "+"
              }
            ],
            "notes": "Neutralize toxin. No immunity from clinical tetanus."
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "procedure",
          "procedureData": {
            "name": "Surgically debride infected source tissue."
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "drugRegimen",
          "regimenData": {
            "intent": "treatment",
            "components": [
              {
                "drug": "Metronidazole",
                "dose": "500 mg",
                "route": "IV",
                "frequency": "q6h"
              },
              {
                "drug": "Metronidazole",
                "dose": "1000 mg",
                "route": "IV",
                "frequency": "q12h",
                "connector": "or"
              },
              {
                "drug": "aqueous Penicillin G",
                "dose": "3 million units",
                "route": "IV",
                "frequency": "q4h",
                "connector": "or"
              }
            ],
            "durationDetail": {
              "fixedDuration": "7-10 days"
            },
            "notes": "See Comment."
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "procedure",
          "procedureData": {
            "name": "Avoid light as may precipitate muscle spasms."
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "drugRegimen",
          "regimenData": {
            "intent": "symptomRelief",
            "components": [
              {
                "drug": "beta blockers, e.g., short acting esmolol"
              }
            ],
            "notes": "To control sympathetic hyperactivity."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Alternative Regimens"
    },
    {
      "type": "drugRegimen",
      "regimenData": {
        "intent": "treatment",
        "components": [
          {
            "drug": "Doxycycline",
            "dose": "100 mg",
            "route": "IV",
            "frequency": "q12h"
          }
        ],
        "durationDetail": {
          "fixedDuration": "7-10 days"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Comments"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Reference: Ann Intern Med 154: 329, 2011 (recommends Metronidazole for 10-14 days); Lancet 393: 1657, 2019."
      ]
    }
  ]
}
